WEBVTT

00:00.273 --> 00:03.807
<i>My name is Michael Westen.
I used to be a spy until...</i>

00:04.660 --> 00:07.195
We got a burn notice
on you. You're blacklisted.

00:07.263 --> 00:09.631
<i>When you're burned, you've got nothing...</i>

00:09.699 --> 00:12.300
<i>no cash, no credit, no job history.</i>

00:12.368 --> 00:14.669
<i>You're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.</i>

00:14.737 --> 00:16.705
- Where am I?
- Miami.

00:16.772 --> 00:19.941
<i>You do whatever work comes your way.</i>

00:20.009 --> 00:22.577
<i>You rely on anyone who's
still talking to you.</i>

00:22.645 --> 00:24.179
<i>A trigger-happy ex-girlfriend...</i>

00:24.246 --> 00:25.814
Should we shoot them?

00:25.881 --> 00:28.383
<i>... An old friend who used to
inform on you to the FBI...</i>

00:28.451 --> 00:30.785
You know spies... a bunch
of bitchy little girls.

00:30.853 --> 00:33.321
<i>- Family, too...
- Hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:33.389 --> 00:35.490
<i>- If you're desperate.
- Someone needs your help, Michael.</i>

00:35.558 --> 00:37.993
<i>Bottom line... as long as you're burned,</i>

00:38.060 --> 00:39.661
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

00:41.000 --> 00:47.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

00:53.676 --> 00:56.678
Mike, I'm telling you, don't do it.

00:56.746 --> 00:58.179
What? You don't like the belt?

00:58.247 --> 01:00.215
I'm not kidding around here.
You got to put a kibosh on this.

01:00.282 --> 01:01.816
Sam, we talked about this.

01:01.884 --> 01:04.218
Well, maybe we didn't
talk about it enough.

01:04.286 --> 01:06.454
You're working for the same sons
of bitches that burned you, Mike,

01:06.522 --> 01:08.056
and now you're gonna
meet with this Vince guy.

01:08.124 --> 01:10.225
- Vaughn.
- Vaughn... good name for a vampire.

01:10.292 --> 01:12.627
I'm just saying, I don't
think you thought this through.

01:12.695 --> 01:14.062
I don't love working with him,

01:14.130 --> 01:15.530
but what we're doing is important.

01:15.598 --> 01:17.265
Why, 'cause Simon got out?

01:17.333 --> 01:19.000
Okay, he was a bad guy.

01:19.068 --> 01:20.869
<i>Okay, a very bad guy.</i>

01:20.936 --> 01:23.571
But he's stuck in a dungeon
somewhere. Problem solved.

01:23.639 --> 01:25.674
If it was just about Simon, maybe,

01:25.741 --> 01:28.610
but the guy who helped him
escape has bigger plans.

01:28.678 --> 01:30.679
I know you feel this is on your shoulders,

01:30.746 --> 01:32.614
but it's not your job to solve everything.

01:32.682 --> 01:33.982
Just walk away.

01:34.050 --> 01:36.251
I got an innocent man
burned for looking into this.

01:36.318 --> 01:37.686
If I stop now,

01:37.753 --> 01:40.655
I'll have ruined Jesse
Porter's life for nothing.

01:40.723 --> 01:41.690
Okay, fine.

01:43.693 --> 01:46.594
But I still think
Vaughn is a vampire name.

01:56.739 --> 01:58.239
Hey, pal.

01:58.307 --> 02:00.909
You're looking well.

02:00.976 --> 02:03.311
Miami sunshine is working wonders for you.

02:03.379 --> 02:06.448
Well, I get a little pasty when
my pals lock me in a secret prison.

02:10.352 --> 02:12.187
So, how's our project coming?

02:12.254 --> 02:15.123
Slowly. I've been looking
through Jesse Porter's files.

02:15.191 --> 02:17.492
It's a few thousand
pages of raw intelligence.

02:17.560 --> 02:19.594
Yeah.

02:19.662 --> 02:21.863
We should talk about Jesse Porter.

02:21.931 --> 02:23.531
What about him?

02:23.599 --> 02:25.366
FBI picked him up, then released him.

02:25.434 --> 02:27.168
They decided it was better to let him go

02:27.236 --> 02:28.436
and keep the incident quiet.

02:28.504 --> 02:30.138
He's been laying low,

02:30.206 --> 02:31.673
making calls to people
around the government

02:31.741 --> 02:35.043
to figure out who stole his files.

02:36.145 --> 02:38.747
He's looking for who burned him.

02:38.814 --> 02:41.049
Don't worry.

02:41.117 --> 02:42.751
We're gonna have him taken care of.

02:42.818 --> 02:43.918
Taken care of?

02:43.986 --> 02:45.587
Look, it's nothing lethal.

02:45.654 --> 02:47.689
We're just gonna find
him and put him on a plane

02:47.757 --> 02:49.557
to a nice, remote holding facility.

02:49.625 --> 02:50.892
Vaughn, that's a mistake.

02:50.960 --> 02:53.061
It's more efficient to
use him as a resource.

02:53.129 --> 02:56.331
So, you sure you're not feeling
sentimental just 'cause you burned him?

02:56.398 --> 02:58.366
No, everything we need
is inside Jesse's head.

02:58.434 --> 03:00.135
You put me in charge of the investigation.

03:00.202 --> 03:02.036
Let me handle Jesse.

03:06.142 --> 03:06.975
Phone records.

03:09.645 --> 03:12.680
Allied financial services?

03:12.748 --> 03:14.482
Yeah, Jesse hacked their PBX switch.

03:14.550 --> 03:16.818
He's using it to make his calls.

03:18.621 --> 03:20.355
Bug it, boss.

03:21.991 --> 03:23.792
That should set you on
the way to locating him.

03:26.061 --> 03:27.996
Just curious... have you thought at all

03:28.063 --> 03:30.765
about what you're gonna say
to Jesse when you find him?

03:30.833 --> 03:33.868
"Hi. I'm Michael. I destroyed your life."

03:33.936 --> 03:36.471
I'll try to avoid that subject.

03:36.539 --> 03:41.209
Has it occurred to you that
avoiding Jesse might be a good idea?

03:41.277 --> 03:43.211
You've toyed with him enough.

03:43.279 --> 03:45.814
I'll do everything I can to help him, Fi.

03:45.881 --> 03:47.649
First I got to find him.

03:48.884 --> 03:52.987
Well, I guess a little Sunday
break-in never hurt anyone.

04:08.270 --> 04:11.206
We got 90 seconds.

04:11.273 --> 04:13.174
You'd be surprised what
I can do in 90 seconds.

04:14.109 --> 04:16.611
<i>Housed in office utility rooms,</i>

04:16.678 --> 04:19.480
<i>a PBX is the phone switchboard
for a whole company.</i>

04:19.548 --> 04:21.382
<i>Using a router with upgraded firmware,</i>

04:21.450 --> 04:23.952
<i>pros can hack them to
make untraceable calls</i>

04:24.019 --> 04:25.587
<i>from the comfort of their own homes.</i>

04:25.654 --> 04:27.755
<i>It's how spies get free long-distance.</i>

04:27.823 --> 04:30.458
<i>Identifying the right line to bug on a PBX</i>

04:30.526 --> 04:32.994
<i>is as simple as matching
call times from your records</i>

04:33.062 --> 04:34.462
<i>to those in the computer.</i>

04:34.530 --> 04:36.264
<i>Of course, if you have to comb</i>

04:36.332 --> 04:37.999
<i>through thousands of phone calls,</i>

04:38.067 --> 04:40.168
<i>it's easier said than done.</i>

04:40.236 --> 04:43.204
<i>Everyone knows spies are good
with languages and firearms,</i>

04:43.272 --> 04:45.974
<i>but they need to be
great storytellers, too.</i>

04:46.041 --> 04:47.976
<i>If you can't keep a break-in secret,</i>

04:48.043 --> 04:50.445
<i>you have to get creative
to cover your tracks.</i>

04:50.512 --> 04:52.780
<i>If a company's just
laid off half its staff,</i>

04:52.848 --> 04:54.382
<i>no one asks many questions</i>

04:54.450 --> 04:56.684
<i>when it looks like an ex-employee</i>

04:56.752 --> 04:58.152
<i>broke in to make a mess.</i>

04:58.220 --> 04:59.454
Taking your sweet time, Michael.

04:59.521 --> 05:01.055
You need to buy us some more time, Fi.

05:08.931 --> 05:10.565
That's our cue to leave, Michael.

05:19.308 --> 05:21.276
What took you so long?

05:23.078 --> 05:24.913
I thought you were gonna buy us more time.

05:24.980 --> 05:26.581
I knew you were gonna say that.

05:33.689 --> 05:35.723
- How was that?
- Very good.

05:35.791 --> 05:37.025
Mm-hmm.

